	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=3064"><span id=" ">Mortiis</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">90 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [1.66]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Tindaini, the correct answer to your question is....<br/><br/>both.<br/><br/><br/>A warrior should be proficient in 1 hand slash and 2 hand slash.&nbsp;&nbsp;Your skill in both should be maxed out.  Some would also say, that you should keep 1 hand blunt, 2 hand blunt, and piercing maxed out as well.  There are good weapons in all five categories useable by warriors that you may come across in your progression to level 60.  At the very least, max out your 1 hand slash and 2 hand slash.  Even if you do get this epic weapon some day, there are situations where the one 2 hand slash weapon is appropriate and others where the two 1 hand slash weapons are appropriate.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
