	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=73587"><span id=" ">Raejin</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">61 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>*nod* -- 2x1HS is good when fighting casters, since you can switch out your secondary with a shield, Bash to interrupt, then switch back; time it right and it won't slow down your dual-wielding double-attacking frenzy at all.<br/><br/>2HS is handy for jousting in PvP, if you're a PvP server or dueling sort -- where nothing but damage matters, since for the most part you'll be running around in circles and even a weighted axe will cycle by the time you swing around and come back.<br/><br/>So yeah. Keep both maxxed at least, and probably the other three as well, just in case a nice item you weren't expecting drops; otherwise you'll have to miss 50,000 times in a row before your skill catches up to a tolerable level.<br/><br/>- R</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
